  "prompt": "What is the difference between human milk and cow milk?",
  "response": "Here are key differences between human milk and cow milk:\n\n1. Nutritional Composition\n- Human milk:\n* Perfectly balanced for infant nutrition\n* Higher lactose content\n* Lower protein concentration\n* Contains immune-boosting antibodies\n* More easily digestible\n\n- Cow milk:\n* Higher protein content\n* Different protein structure\n* Lower lactose percentage\n* Lower fat content\n* Lacks human antibodies\n\n2. Protein Types\n- Human milk: More whey proteins\n- Cow milk: More casein proteins\n\n3. Immune Properties\n- Human milk: Contains living immune cells and antibodies\n- Cow milk: Limited immune protection\n\n4. Fat Composition\n- Human milk: Higher percentage of brain-development essential fatty acids\n- Cow milk: Different fat profile\n\n5. Adaptation\n- Human milk: Specifically designed for human infant development\n- Cow milk: Designed for cow calf growth\n\n6. Digestibility\n- Human milk: Easily digestible for human infants\n- Cow milk: More difficult for infant digestion\n\n7. Nutrient Concentration\n- Human milk: Changes composition based on infant's needs\n- Cow milk: More consistent, static composition\n\nThese differences explain why pediatricians recommend human milk or specialized infant formula for babies.",
